  "title": "Plan de la Basse-Terre et de la Rade de la Tortue",
  "survey_basis": "No reliable town survey exists; composed from Exquemelin's description, du Casse-era French colonial memoirs, and the engraved plans of Fort de Rocher (1640s). By 1730 the place is a backwater of turtlers and small planters \u2014 the government long since removed to Saint-Domingue. Coastline placed against the real south shore of \u00cele de la Tortue; town layout is plausible infill.",
